 put strong upper\nlimits on the SFR at z>1: e.g., if beta>2 then the SFR for 1<z<5 scales as\n(1+z)^alpha with alpha<2. This is equivalent to stating that no more than 80%\nof stars in the Universe formed at z>1. Our results are consistent with the\nbest-fit results from compilations of cosmic SFR estimates based on UV\nluminosity density, which give 1.8<beta<2.9 and -1.0<alpha<0.7, and are also\nconsistent with estimates of Omega_stars based on the K-band luminosity\ndensity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Oct 2001 21:56:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Jan 2002 20:21:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-03-10"}
