{"id":"cond-mat/0110631","submitter":"Paola Paci","authors":"P. Paci, E. Cappelluti, C. Grimaldi and L. Pietronero","title":"Nonadiabatic Superconductivity and Vertex Corrections in Uncorrelated\n  Systems","comments":"4 pages, 3 eps figs","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B 65, 012512 (2002)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.65.012512","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.supr-con","license":null,"abstract":"  We investigate the issue of the nonadiabatic superconductivity in\nuncorrelated systems. A local approximation is employed coherently with the\nweak dependence on the involved momenta. Our results show that nonadiabatic\nvertex corrections are never negligible, but lead to a strong suppression of\n$T_c$ with respect to the conventional theory. This feature is understood in\nterms of the momentum-frequency dependence of the vertex function. In contrast\nto strongly correlated systems, where the small ${\\bf q}$-selection probes the\npositive part of vertex function, vertex corrections in uncorrelated systems\nare essentially negative resulting in an effective reduction of the\nsuperconducting pairing. Our analysis shows that vertex corrections in\nnonadiabatic regime can be never disregarded independently of the degree of\nelectronic correlation in the system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Oct 2001 16:01:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
